SIMPLE: cupboard
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cupboard
<hw>Cup"board</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧b"b⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cup
+ <ets>board</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A board or shelf for cups
and dishes.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small closet in a room, with shelves to receive
cups, dishes, food, etc.; hence, any small closet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cupboard love</b></col>, <cd>interested love, or that
which has an eye to the cupboard.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>cupboard love</xex>
is seldom true.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Poor Robin.</au> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> --
<col><b>To cry cupboard</b></col>, <cd>to call for food; to express
hunger.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧My stomach cries
cupboard.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>W. Irving.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cupboard</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cupboard
<hw>Cup"board</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To collect, as into a
cupboard; to hoard.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cupel</ent>⟦br⟧
